I have to agree with anqxyr. I think that there's a good kernel here, but there needs to be way more detail for an SCP as ambitious in scope as this one. There's a foundation embassy established for twelve years, but there's only only information about a few  subtypes of this scp.

Where's the more accessible general information? What's the capital city? Are there cities? We know that it's an empire with an empress, but who is the empress? Is she a  analogous to ours, but are there any major differences? Has there been any sort of information/technology sharing? For example, satellites are a Big Deal for our civilization, but Antarctica is about the worst place for launching spacecraft and having satellite coverage. Does this civilization bother? If they have satellites, what do they actually know of the world outside (despite being typically insular)

Hell, how have the people of SCP-1483 treated the existence of the foundation, and the existence of another (nominally) friendly plane of existence? Is their existence considered a secret similar to how the foundation would keep secret SCP-1483, or are they generally accepted? Is the foundation  itself a secret?

It really feels like an entry as ambitious in scope as this one needs to be significantly fleshed out. Compare this with the entries for SCP-093, another  entry, where the foundation has a very limited amount of information due to the sheer danger involved in travelling there.







